    AbstractRemoteConnection

    public class AbstractRemoteConnection.JsonValueResponseHandler
extends AbstractRemoteConnection.AbstractJsonValueResponseHandler<org.forgerock.json.JsonValue>
    A ResponseHandler that returns the response body as a JsonValue for successful (2xx) responses. If the response code was >= 300, the response body is consumed and an AbstractRemoteConnection.HttpResponseResourceException is thrown.

    If this is used with HttpClient.execute(org.apache.http.client.methods.HttpUriRequest, org.apache.http.client.ResponseHandler) , HttpClient may handle redirects (3xx responses) internally.
